  "market_context": "USD/JPY daily chart in late November 2023 after price rallied to around 151.500–152.000 forming buy stops, then swept those highs and displaced aggressively lower, leaving a bearish order block zone around 149.000–149.500.",
  "key_observation": "After the displacement lower, an up-close candle retraces into the bearish order block and closes below its opening price, forming a propulsion block. Price respects the opening price, fails to reach the mean threshold, then continues lower.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify that price swept buy stops at the prior highs near 151.500 and then displaced lower, leaving a volume imbalance.",
    "Step 2: Wait to see price react out of the volume imbalance / order block area around 149.000–149.500.",
    "Step 3: Observe an up-close candle delivering back into that important bearish order block area.",
    "Step 4: Confirm a closure below the opening price of that up-close candle, forming a propulsion block.",
    "Step 5: Watch for sensitivity at the opening price and require that price does not break or close above the mean threshold of the propulsion block.",
    "Step 6: With the opening price respected and the mean threshold not breached, anticipate continuation lower."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price respected the opening price, did not reach the mean threshold, and continued lower as expected (no specific R target stated for this example).",
  "lessons": "A propulsion block forms when an up-close candle retraces into a bearish order block and closes below its opening price. The opening price must remain sensitive and the mean threshold must hold for the continuation lower to remain valid.",
